 to Muslim Al-Nawawi\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":25521,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2017\/12\/01\/al-muwalah-fi-al-wudu-wajib\/","url_meta":{"origin":25570,"position":3},"title":"Hadith on Wudu: Evidence continuity in ablution is obligatory","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"December 1, 2017","format":false,"excerpt":"Umar ibn al-Khattab reported: A man performed ablution and he left out a spot on his foot the size of a fingernail. The Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cGo back and perform ablution well.\u201d The man went back and then prayed. Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Muslim 243 Grade: Sahih\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":13129,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2013\/03\/25\/not-rushing-through-wudu\/","url_meta":{"origin":25570,"position":4},"title":"Hadith on Wudu: Taking care not to rush through ablution","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"March 25, 2013","format":false,"excerpt":"Abdullah ibn Amr reported: We returned with the Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, from Mecca to Medina, until we found water by the road. Some people hurried to perform ablution for afternoon prayer, by the time we reached them their heels were dry and had not\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645","link":"https: